HEADWORD: Amphiscians
<hw>Am*phis"cians</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ throwing a
shadow both ways; <grk>'amfi`</grk> + <?/ shadow.]</ety> <def>The
inhabitants of the tropic, whose shadows in one part of the year are
cast to the north, and in the other to the south, according as the sun
is south or north of their zenith.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amphistomous</ent>⟦br⟧
